The paper discusses semantic word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also presents a generative language model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methodological twist of solving the model in closed form suggests the use of mathematical techniques, which could fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses experiments to support the efficacy of the word embeddings, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
